(9, 2, 'Mega V2 (125-250kVA) UPS  ', 'Mega V2 Modular 125 – 250KVA UPS System Characteristics    Enhanced power modules of 25kVA/kW (PF=1)   Provide improved tier 2', 'c34bde85a9650a010fad422cb134f36f.jpg', 'aa672d49beb9c223c20af5d2d896e7a6.pdf', '<p><strong>Mega V2 Modular 125 &ndash; 250KVA UPS&nbsp;<strong>System Characteristics</strong></strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li><img alt="" src="http://www.gamatronic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/Mega-V2-small.jpg" style="float:right; height:375px; margin:0px 0px 0px 10px; width:156px" />&nbsp;<strong>Enhanced power modules of 25kVA/kW (PF=1)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Provide improved tier 2 serviceability with quick &amp; convenient local maintenance.</p>\n\n<p>The new Mega V2 module provides the same MTTR to users while allowing for the local partners substantial savings.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li><strong>Substantial decreased module weight.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The new mechanical design of the Mega V2 module is 2.5 kg lighter.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li><strong>State of the art controller offering.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li>Log download&nbsp; to users&rsquo; PC allows for an improved online serviceability.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li>Additional language selection.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li>Real time e mail notification.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li>Professional server shutdown.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li>Frequency converter feature.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The UPS system can be utilized to convert the frequency of the mains power supply from 50 HZ to 60 HZ vice versa</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="list-style-type:none">\n	<li><strong>Up to 10 modules in a system</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>3U high, 19&Prime; wide modules</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Advanced IGBT technologies</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Centralized ST/SW and batteries</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>7&Prime; touch screen for operating the system</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Internal computer for control &amp; management</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Especially high efficiency of 96%</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Minimum floor space per Watt</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table style="width:720px">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Topology</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">True on-line, double conversion, VFI</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Construction</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Modular, parallel hot-swapped modules</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table style="width:720px">\n	<thead>\n		<tr>\n			<th colspan="2" style="background-color:rgb(230, 238, 238); vertical-align:baseline">INPUT</th>\n		</tr>\n	</thead>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Voltage</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">3 X 400 Vac + N</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">Voltage range</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">-20 % and +15 %</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Current</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">3x42 A per module - no inrush current at startup</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">Frequency</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">47&divide;63 Hz</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Power walk-in</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">&gt;60 sec</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">Power factor</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">0.99</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">THDI</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">&lt;5 %</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table style="width:720px">\n	<thead>\n		<tr>\n			<th colspan="2" style="background-color:rgb(230, 238, 238); vertical-align:baseline">OUTPUT</th>\n		</tr>\n	</thead>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Rated power</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">25 kVA / 25 kW to 500 kVA / 500kW</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">Frequency (in free-running mode)</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">50/60 Hz &plusmn;0.1 %</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Frequency tracking range</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">&plusmn;0.5 Hz, &plusmn;1 Hz, &plusmn;2 Hz, &plusmn;3 Hz (selectable)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">Slew rate</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 246); vertical-align:top">1 Hz / sec</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">Voltage</td>\n			<td style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align:top">3x400 Vac + N</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td style="ba